The PathPlanner app works great under MacOS. Thank you for that! When running under MS Windows, however, we can’t seem to manipulate the Endpoint of the trajectory. It seems to select (turn orange), and the box with x, y, position, etc. pops up. But none of the handles work. We can’t move the Endpoint, rotate it, mess with its control points, etc. Changes entered manually are honored, but that doesn’t give access to all its knobs.

The Starting point and waypoints work just fine.

We tried this with both Windows 10 and 11.

Are we doing something wrong?

See this note from earlier today:

PathPlanner 2023 Beta Technical
PSA to anyone that updates to the version released earlier today: there is a bug preventing the end point of a path from being dragged around. You can work around this by adding another point to the end, dragging the old end point, then deleting the extra point. Will try to get this fixed ASAP but likely won’t be today.
